30/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The security situation in Macedonia is improving, Director of the Intelligence Agency Dosta Dimovska said Wednesday (29 January). While describing the overall situation as calm, she urged more efficient co-operation between the intelligence and counter-intelligence services. Also Wednesday, NATO, EU and OSCE representatives in Macedonia held a joint news conference, declaring the international community is generally satisfied with the security situation in the country.
In other news, Macedonia authorities announced Wednesday they would extradite notorious Bulgarian banker Ivan Mironov to Sofia. Nabbed last month, Mironov is charged with misappropriating some 100m euros while serving as executive director of Bulgaria's bankrupt Balkanbank. (Utrinski Vesnik - 30/01/03; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, Mediapool - 29/01/03)
